        <num>CC 1921</num>
        <heading>1921.  Rescission of contract for incapacity</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1921.  Rescission of contract for incapacity
Upon rescission of a contract on the ground of incapacity, each party or his legal representative shall restore to the other what he has received thereunder.  When restoration is impossible or impracticable, the court may award compensation to the party to whom restoration cannot be made.</p>
        </content>
